Here are some useful commands for github

//Install git on your computer (linux)
sudo apt-get install git

// Global setup
git config --global user.name "USERNAME"
git config --global user.email "EMAIL"

//create a local repo on your machine
git init <REPOSITORY>

//select your project/repo from your account
git remote add origin https://github.com/jh27539/<PROJECT>.git

//in case you type the wrong one by accident
git remote set-url origin https://github.com/jh27539/<PROJECT>.git

//add a file to your repo
git add <FILENAME>

//add all files in the current directory
git add *

//commit and use a comment
git commit -m "commentUpdates"

//Push to online github
git push -u origin master

If you already have a project to push on your computer,
1 - set up a repo on github with the same name
2 - navigate to that directory on your pc
3 - remote add origin
4 - git push -u origin master
